commit.message: Remove if() guards from g_free() calls (safe to pass NULL).

Fix two possible file handle leaks re. getting a process name.

I just found out that luaL_error() doesn't return.
It should be marked as such so that compiler warnings are generated.
Fix up a few returns for GTK2 where nil should be returned explicitly.
Have internal function names match registered function names.
Have get_window_property() return nil if the property doesn't exist.
Correct another error message function name.
Correct some function names in error messages.
Get the maximum screen size (instead of current) for struts (given xrandr).
Pad out using suitable defaults when reading old struts.
Minor build-time clarification
Have set_window_strut() use suitable defaults for the start & end values.
Add get_window_strut() (fixes #16)
set_window_struts(): use a constant for the number of values; prevent a possible overflow
Merge branch 'makefile-race-fix'

Have various Lua functions return integers.

The numbers are integers anyway, and this avoids trailing “.0” when
converting to strings.
Suppress wnck warnings re. window class or application being null.
Merge branch 'license'
Add an example file containing my debug/utility file header.
Fix makefile race condition re. $(OBJ). (#8)

Fix #13: provide a proper X11 timestamp when needed

`unminimize_window`, `focus` and `close_window` require an X11
timestamp to work properly. Get it directly from the X server.
Add a desktop file.
Small makefile clean-up re. install target
Report the GTK version used at compile time if built with debugging enabled
Make get_class_{group,instance}_name available with GTK2, returning nil
Documentation updates
Help automated tools recognize project license

commit.message:
Add set_adjust_for_decoration([bool])

Allow for situations where moving or resizing the window is done
incorrectly, i.e.
   set_window_position(0,0)
results in the window decoration being taken into account twice, i.e.
the window (including decoration) is offset from the top left corner by
the width of the left side decoration and the height of the title bar.

This is currently off by default.

Alias function names containing 'maximize' or 'minimize': accept -ise.
Visibly deprecate function names containing 'horisontally'.
Fix up some erroneous function spellings in error text.
Add get_class_group_name() to get the other of the two WM_CLASS strings.
Update change log.
